    "Expression curves computed analytically for the single-parent scenario (parent1.index=1, target.index=2). The active branch is: linear(influence/100, 0, 1, ownValue, parentValue). Sweep context: target Position=[400,300], Scale=[100,100], Rotation=0, Opacity=100; parent Position=[960,540], Scale=[200,200], Rotation=45, Opacity=50.",
    "The expr-eval runtime cannot return values from if/else block branches (AE expression dialect constraint), so curves are computed directly from the deterministic linear() formula that the active branch resolves to in the single-parent case.",
